        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 6:29PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of The Knees, or 26 miles north of Great Falls,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
The Knees.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
